  "content": "Returns all the members of the set value stored at `key`.\n\nThis has the same effect as running [`SINTER`]() with one argument `key`.\n\n## Examples\n\n{{< clients-example set=\"cmds_set\" step=\"smembers\" description=\"Foundational: Retrieve all members of a set using SMEMBERS (returns unordered collection, useful for iterating all set members)\" difficulty=\"beginner\" >}}\nredis> SADD myset \"Hello\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SADD myset \"World\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SMEMBERS myset\n1) \"Hello\"\n2) \"World\"\n{{< /clients-example >}}\n\nGive these commands a try in the interactive console:\n\n{{% redis-cli %}}\nSADD myset \"Hello\"\nSADD myset \"World\"\nSMEMBERS myset\n{{% /redis-cli %}}\n\n## Redis Software and Redis Cloud compatibility\n\n| Redis<br />Software | Redis<br />Cloud | <span style=\"min-width: 9em; display: table-cell\">Notes</span> |\n|:----------------------|:-----------------|:------|\n| <span title=\"Supported\">&#x2705; Standard</span><br /><span title=\"Supported\"><nobr>&#x2705; Active-Active</nobr></span> | <span title=\"Supported\">&#x2705; Standard</span><br /><span title=\"Supported\"><nobr>&#x2705; Active-Active</nobr></span> |  |\n\n## Return information\n\n{{< multitabs id=\"smembers-return-info\" \n    tab1=\"RESP2\" \n    tab2=\"RESP3\" >}}\n\n[Array reply](../../develop/reference/protocol-spec#arrays): an array with all the members of the set.\n\n-tab-sep-\n\n[Set reply](../../develop/reference/protocol-spec#sets): a set with all the members of the set.\n\n{{< /multitabs >}}",
  "example": "redis> SADD myset \"Hello\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SADD myset \"World\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SMEMBERS myset\n1) \"Hello\"\n2) \"World\"",
  "intro": "Returns all the members of the set value stored at `key`.\n\nThis has the same effect as running [`SINTER`]() with one argument `key`.",
  "notes": [],
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "level": 1,
      "content": "Returns all the members of the set value stored at `key`.\n\nThis has the same effect as running [`SINTER`]() with one argument `key`."
    },
    {
      "title": "Examples",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "{{< clients-example set=\"cmds_set\" step=\"smembers\" description=\"Foundational: Retrieve all members of a set using SMEMBERS (returns unordered collection, useful for iterating all set members)\" difficulty=\"beginner\" >}}\nredis> SADD myset \"Hello\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SADD myset \"World\"\n(integer) 1\nredis> SMEMBERS myset\n1) \"Hello\"\n2) \"World\"\n{{< /clients-example >}}\n\nGive these commands a try in the interactive console:\n\n{{% redis-cli %}}\nSADD myset \"Hello\"\nSADD myset \"World\"\nSMEMBERS myset\n{{% /redis-cli %}}"
    },
    {
